  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the <strong>air fryer</strong> to 200°C, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Add a handful of <strong>flour </strong>to a plate and a splash of <strong>milk </strong>to a small bowl, then add the <strong>panko breadcrumbs </strong>to a separate plate with the <strong>ground paprika</strong></p><p>Chop the <strong>chicken breast strips</strong> in half, lengthways, then season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1675250551778-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1675250551778-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1675250551778-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1675250551778-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1675250551778-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Coat the <strong>chicken strips</strong> in the <strong>flour</strong>, tap off any excess, then add them to the <strong>milk </strong>and finally press them into the <strong>breadcrumbs </strong>firmly to evenly coat all over</p><p>Add the <strong>breaded chicken strips </strong>to the <strong>air fryer basket</strong> and spray generously with <strong>olive oil</strong>, then cook for 10-12 min, turning halfway (air fryer cooking times may vary), or until golden and cooked through (no pink meat!) – these are your <strong>chicken goujons</strong></p><p>Tip: Air fryers work best when the food is spaced out in a single layer. You may need to do this in batches!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1675250554717-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1675250554717-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1675250554717-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1675250554717-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-2-1675250554717-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the chicken is cooking, cut the <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into small bite-sized pieces</p><p>Add the<strong> chopped potatoes</strong> to a large heatproof bowl, then cover the bowl with <strong>cling film</strong> and pierce a few holes in the top with a fork</p><p>Put the bowl in the <strong>microwave</strong> for 6-7 min <span class=\"text-danger\">[8-10 min]</span> or until the potatoes are fork-tender</p><p>Boil half a kettle</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
